"Here is your new Python coding question:\n\n{\"title\": \"Easy: Even-Indexed Elements\", \n\"description\": \"Write a function that takes as input a list of integers and returns the sum of all even-indexed elements. If the list has an odd length, consider the middle element to be the one at index `(length - 1) // 2`. For example, if the input is `[1, 3, 5, 7]`, the function should return `6`, because only the first and third elements are even-indexed.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef sum_even_indexed_elements(lst: list[int]) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `lst` (list[int]): A list of integers.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the sum of all even-indexed elements in the input list.\", \n\"code\": \"def sum_even_indexed_elements(lst: list[int]) -> int:\\n    return sum(lst[i] for i in range(0, len(lst), 2)),\\n\", \n\"tests\": [\"assert sum_even_indexed_elements([1, 3, 5, 7]) == 6\", \"assert sum_even_indexed_elements([2, 4, 6, 8, 10]) == 20\"]}"